news.title: Call grows for five year structural audits of high-rises in Noida
news.para: A NCF team met Praveen Mishra, the additio-nal CEO of the Noida Authority, on Wednesday to press for their demand of the structural audit in view of several incidents of plasters peeling off highrise buildings in Noida in the recent past.

news.title: Malls start charging full rentals, end concessions
news.para: Unfair to charge pre-Covid rentals as some businesses have not become fully operational, say tenants.

news.title: Kajol buys two apartments in Juhu worth Rs 11.95 crore
news.para: According to Squarefeetindia, the actress purchased the two flats situated on the 10th floor of the building. The report further stated that the combined cost of the two properties is Rs 11.95 crore.

news.title: Shobha Aggarwal of Viney Equity buys bungalow in Delhi for Rs 80 crore
news.para: The bungalow has been sold by Ashok Kumar Mehra of Mehrasons jeweller. Post the reopening of registry offices earlier this month, South Delhi has seen spate of high value transactions. Data accessed from Zapkey.com confirmed that registry happened on February 9.

news.title: Maharashtra: 419 developers opt for e-registration in four months
news.para: Of these 419 applications, 347 have been approved by the registration and town planning authorities and nearly 300 documents have been registered.

news.title: Canadian home prices smash records in January, new starts dip
news.para: The national average selling price hit a new high at C$748,450 ($588,589) in January, up 4.9% on the month and 21% higher from a year earlier, the Canadian Real Estate Association said.

news.title: European Central Bank warns about vulnerable property market in euro zone
news.para: Central bankers have been ringing alarm bells about the euro zone's booming property market that has a decade of ultra-low interest rates and light-touch prudential regulation have helped create.

news.title: Shimao Group plans to extend $947 million trust loan payments by two years: Sources
news.para: Shimao proposed to repay the principal and interest of the trust loan in question - of which 1.3 billion yuan will become due on Thursday, and the rest later this year - in stages in the coming three years, the sources said.

news.title: Mumbai: Court grants bail to Rana Kapoor, Gautam Thapar, others in property sale case
news.para: The present case pertains to allegations in the sale of a property situated on Amrita Shergill Marg in Delhi to a company owned by Rana Kapoor's wife, Bindu Kapoor, for which a separate FIR had been registered by the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) in Mumbai last year.

news.title: China courts freeze $157 million of Evergrande assets over missed construction payments
news.para: Separately, Shanghai Construction Group said last week a local court in Guangzhou has frozen 361.5 million yuan of assets of a different Evergrande unit in the central province of Jiangsu for overdue payments.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces buys 35 acres land in Pune for Rs 100 crore
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces will develop a luxury villas project with a development potential of 1.3 million square feet. This will be the second residential project in the city.

news.title: Gurugram: NBCC Green View declared unsafe, to be demolished
news.para: Yadav said the Government of India enterprise will provide alternate accommodation to the residents. It will also provide rent for those willing to move to flats of their choice with the same parameters, he said.

news.title: Rs 200 crore due, Ghaziabad civic body to seek house tax from government departments
news.para: Among the major defaulters are the electricity department, which has accrued Rs 84.88 crore dues till the current financial year, followed by the Delhi Metro Rail Corporation which owes Rs 45.74 crore.

news.title: Centre grants Rs 20 crore for Nashik's IT park project
news.para: Kulkarni told reporters that on March 1, the Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) is organising a conference on the IT sector, which will be chaired by Union minister of micro, small and medium enterprises Narayan Rane.

news.title: UP RERA imposes penalty of over Rs 1 crore 40 lakh on nine developers
news.para: The penalty has been imposed against AIMS Promoters, Wave Mega City Centre, Ansal Housing and Ansal Properties & Infrastructure, Antriksh Realtech, AVP Realty, ATS Realty, Krishna Estate Developers, Ratan Buildtech and Redicon Infrastructure & Housing.
